parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to not engage or lock, leaving the occupant unrestrained, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not lock
the male portion of the buckle will not engage with the female portion
the buckle is inoperative due to plastic pieces falling inside
a piece of plastic breaks off and remains lodged inside the buckle
the buckle does not engage leaving the occupant unrestrained.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine overheating issue can cause the speedometer to malfunction, leading to a potential safety risk as the vehicle may shut off while in motion, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer needle wavers up and down
the engine temperature gauge is in the red zone
the vehicle may stall or shut off
emission control system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine backfire can cause a fire to start, posing a significant risk to the vehicle occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The engine backfires
a fire starts in the engine compartment
smoke or flames are visible
the vehicle may stall or shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver seat frame can cause the seat to become unstable or even collapse, which can lead to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The driver seat suddenly feels unstable or loose
the seat frame breaks or cracks
the seat becomes difficult to adjust or move
the seat collapses or falls apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of weld joints can cause structural components to break or separate, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or vehicle instability.
symptoms: Unusual noises or creaking sounds from the vehicle's frame or body
visible cracks or breaks in weld joints
sudden loss of structural integrity.
